  "text": "Prostate-specific antigen (PSA) remains the only wellvalidated biomarker for stratification by risk of recurrence in routine clinical use for prostate cancer. The absence of additional biomarkers predicting recurrence has prompted researchers to develop predictive tools based on statistical models using disease features. Among the strategies for risk stratification is the use of nomograms. Nomograms are models that predict outcomes using specific clinical, pathologic, and patient information for each individual patient [CITATION_1] . Our working hypothesis is that genome copy number profiles can define genotypes that predict a patient's risk of postoperative disease recurrence and metastasis and that these genotypes can be incorporated into nomograms thus increasing their accuracy.",
